title: "Attempt to subtract with overflow" in `suggest_moving_args_from_assoc_fn_to_trait_for_qualified_path`

labels.name: E-easy
labels.description: Call for participation: Experience needed to fix: Easy / not much (good first issue)

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
Found with a [modified fuzz-rustc](https://github.com/jruderman/fuzz-rustc) ### Code ICEs iff the compiler is built with overflow checks: ```Rust fn main() { let x = not_found; simd_gt::<()>(x); } ``` ### Error output ``` error[E0425]: cannot find value `not_found` in this scope thread 'rustc' panicked at 'attempt to subtract with overflow', compiler/rustc_hir_analysis/src/structured_errors/wrong_number_of_generic_args.rs:731:44 ```
